response.about:
I consider myself a collectioner, collecting luscious minds and ardent knowledge as would folklore’s Liches collect forbidden spells and artifacts with ecumenical significance. When I was a child I sought clarity of a mind with zeal and ardor blinding me to colourful aspects of the world. That path had led me to conquering abstractness of thought so-desired by scholars, but cast me away from reality in its practicalities and, what’s worse, its heart. Soon I have recognized my malaise in its apathy to everything but abstract mechanisms and begun the quest to reconstruct my own wit. And now my present self is a product of artificial cognitive structure I still proceed to engineer, seeking and collecting valuable mental components discovered by ingenious human beings. This collection of patterns allows me to establish compounds of various minds in collective serving as a core for their interaction and march onward. All of that for a single purpose to unveil arcana of our universe solving the most complex challenges of humanity.

Pompous speeches aside, I am an engineering manager with expertise in Machine Learning and Biotechnology who leads R&D teams at scale to build revolutionary products. I am the former CEO/CTO and Co-Founder of ApexQubit, a Berkeley-based quantum machine learning startup with stellar advisors in pharmaceuticals and quantum computing: Nick Pullen, Barry Sanders and Andris Ambainis. In the past, I had the pleasure to be a part of Entrepreneur First (backed by Reid Hoffman and Demis Hassabis) and Creative Destruction Lab (working with Xanadu, D-wave and Google X).

In my role as Principal Machine Learning Architect at InData Labs I oversee our products or so-called solutions, long-term strategy or structure and, most importantly, our engineering team of 25 machine learning engineers and scientists. As a Principal Machine Learning Scientist at Quantori, I guide our R&D efforts in building Large Medical Models on Electronic Health Records and teach deep learning to engineering teams at scale.
